definitions.definition: To complete , to bring to perfection , to make whole .
examples: We believe your addition will complement the team.

definitions.definition: To provide what the partner lacks and lack what the partner provides , thus forming part of a whole.
examples: The flavors of the pepper and garlic complement each other, giving a very rich taste in combination.
I believe our talents really complement each other.

definitions.definition: To change a voltage , number , color , etc. to its complement.
